Context I was first introduced to the concept of risk by a co-worker when faced with the task to help manage a project for the first time of my career.
He wanted to know all the tasks that had to be done to complete a project, and which of those were particularly risky.
By risk, he meant anything unexpected that could impact the project, and especially the deadline: tasks that cannot be estimated, out of our control, too uncertain&hellip;
